    <h1 class="heading1">Neurosurgery Department at Aatura Hospital</h1>
    <h4 class="heading4">At Aatura Hospital, our Neurosurgery Department is dedicated to providing advanced surgical care for conditions affecting the brain, spine, and nervous system. Led by a team of highly skilled neurosurgeons and supported by specialized healthcare professionals, we offer comprehensive diagnostic, surgical, and rehabilitative services to address a wide range of neurosurgical conditions.</h4>

    <div class="content1">
        <div class="content-left">
            <h3>Our Services</h3>
            <h4>Brain Tumor Surgery</h4>
            <p>We specialize in the surgical treatment of brain tumors, including both benign and malignant tumors. Our neurosurgeons utilize advanced surgical techniques, such as microsurgery, stereotactic radiosurgery, and intraoperative imaging, to safely remove tumors while preserving neurological function and maximizing patient outcomes.</p>

            <h4>Spinal Surgery</h4>
            <p>We offer a wide range of spinal surgery procedures to treat conditions affecting the spine, including herniated discs, spinal stenosis, degenerative disc disease, spinal deformities, and spinal cord injuries. Our neurosurgeons perform minimally invasive spine surgery, spinal fusion, disc replacement, and spinal cord stimulation to relieve pain, improve mobility, and restore spinal stability.</p>

            <h4>Cerebrovascular Surgery</h4>
            <p>We specialize in the surgical treatment of cerebrovascular disorders, including aneurysms, arteriovenous malformations (AVMs), and stroke. Our neurosurgeons perform endovascular procedures, microvascular surgery, and bypass surgery to treat cerebrovascular conditions and prevent complications such as bleeding, stroke, and neurological deficits.</p>

            <h4>Peripheral Nerve Surgery</h4>
            <p>We offer surgical treatment for peripheral nerve disorders, including nerve compression syndromes (carpal tunnel syndrome, cubital tunnel syndrome), nerve injuries, and nerve tumors. Our neurosurgeons perform nerve decompression, nerve repair, and nerve grafting procedures to restore nerve function and alleviate pain and disability.</p>

            <h4>Epilepsy Surgery</h4>
            <p>We provide surgical treatment options for patients with drug-resistant epilepsy who are not responsive to medication. Our neurosurgeons perform epilepsy surgery, including resective surgery, laser ablation, and vagus nerve stimulation (VNS), to reduce seizure frequency and improve quality of life for patients with epilepsy.</p>

            <h4>Functional Neurosurgery</h4>
            <p>We offer functional neurosurgery procedures to treat movement disorders, psychiatric disorders, and chronic pain conditions. Our neurosurgeons perform deep brain stimulation (DBS), stereotactic radiosurgery, and neuroablative procedures to alleviate symptoms and improve quality of life for patients with Parkinson's disease, essential tremor, obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD), and chronic pain syndromes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-right"></div>
    </div>

